{{Refimprove|date=June 2014}} The '''National Railway Museum of New Zealand''' ('''NRM''') is being built<ref name="nzrailmuseum1">{{cite web|url=http://www.nzrailmuseum.com/news/# |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 28, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140712022548/http://www.nzrailmuseum.com/news/ |archivedate=July 12, 2014 }}</ref> to show the history of the [[New Zealand]] railways. Work is underway to open at [[Ferrymead Heritage Park]] in [[Ferrymead]], [[Christchurch]] by the end of 2015 at the site of [[Ferrymead Railway|New Zealand's first railway]] opened in 1863.<ref name="NRMNZ">{{cite web| url=http://www.nzrailmuseum.com/ | title=National Railway Museum of New Zealand|website=Nzrailmuseum.com | accessdate=16 June 2014}}</ref>
The museum owns one electric locomotive from [[Wellington]], one electric multiple unit also from Wellington and three wagons with a leased diesel shunter. The museum will also other [[New Zealand Railways Department|NZR]] and Bush locomotives from the [[Canterbury Railway Society]]. The museum will also display other rolling stock including a turntable from [[Auckland]] and any other suitable railway material. The museum is still being built with the turntable in place.<ref name="nzrailmuseum1"/>
